<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S. STRATEGY FOR NUCLEAR RESPONSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I want to thank Toth for his chilling three-part series. Coupled with the 
(Northrop) ad on Page 7 for the stealth bomber, it made quite an impression on 
me. I am in disbelief. I really believed that the era of the Evil Empire of the 
Soviet Union was over. Obviously, I have been in a dream world. The scenes of 
President Reagan and President Gorbachev signing the nuclear missile reduction 
agreement, the words of President Bush about moving toward de-escalation of 
tension are vivid but apparently illusory. 
</P>
<P>
We must as citizens of this planet speak out. The leadership of this country 
needs desperately to hear from us. Please write or phone your representatives 
and let them know how you feel about the $305-billion defense budget. 
</P>
<P>
FLORENCE HORGAN 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
