<P>
On Oct. 1, the beach in Corona del Mar will be the site of an invitational 
sandcastle sculpting competition for architects, landscape architects and other 
affiliated professionals, sponsored by the Orange County chapter of the 
American Institute of Architects. The public is invited to watch the 
proceedings: sculpting from 10 a.m. to 3 p.m., awards at 4 p.m. Winners will be 
chosen on the basis of originality of design, best use of site and degree of 
difficulty. Funds raised through entry fees and community sponsorship will 
support OCCAIA activities. For more information, call Jeff Smith at Richard 
Lewis Architects at (714) 549-2800 or the OCCAIA office at (714) 557-7796. 
</P>
