<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ATTORNEY KISSED EX-CLIENT, COURT TOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Celebrity divorce lawyer Marvin Mitchelson was seen at least twice in public 
kissing and hugging a woman who is suing him for legal malpractice, a friend of 
the plaintiff testified Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Mitchelson, 61, who introduced the term "palimony" to jurisprudence, testified 
earlier in the day at his Los Angeles Superior Court trial that he could not 
recall meeting the witness, Cheryl Christiansen. Christiansen testified on 
behalf of her friend, Felicia Gordon, who is suing Mitchelson, accusing him of 
bungling her multimillion-dollar divorce from businessman Robert MacDonald in 
1982 and of taking advantage of her emotional and financial distress to 
pressure her into having sex with him. 
</P>
<P>
Christiansen testified that at a 1983 birthday party for Gordon in Beverly 
Hills, she saw Mitchelson grab Gordon and pull her down next to him on a sofa. 
"At the party," Christiansen said, "he was kissing her on a number of occasions 
and he had his arm around her waist." 
</P>
