SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former probation officer at Juvenile Hall was ordered Monday to stand trial 
on charges of molesting 10 girls he had contact with while they were 
incarcerated. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Denny, 48, of San Diego, was bound over to Superior Court after a 
daylong preliminary hearing conducted by San Diego Municipal Judge Nicholas 
Kasimatis. Denny is charged with six felony sex charges and 14 misdemeanor 
counts of unlawfully touching the girls, all minors. 
</P>
<P>
The judge dismissed some counts when some of the witnesses failed to show up or 
the prosecution did not present evidence on those counts. 
</P>
