<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
FULLERTON TEACHER JOINS EDUCATION TASK FORCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ginger Britt, a teacher at Laguna Road Elementary School in Fullerton, has been 
selected to serve on the 35-member Elementary Grades Task Force just created by 
state schools Supt. Bill Honig. 
</P>
<P>
The primary role of the task force will be to make specific recommendations for 
improving the educational program provided to California's elementary-grade 
students, Honig said in a press release. 
</P>
<P>
The elementary task force comes two years after another committee studied 
middle schools and produced a report titled "Caught in the Middle," which led 
to a variety of reforms in middle schools throughout the nation, Honig said. 
</P>
<P>
The elementary task force will meet five times in the next year and will 
conduct several public hearings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
