EASTERN ADDS PILOTS, MORE FLIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ATLANTA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eastern Airlines, crippled for months by a machinists' strike, increased its 
daily flights from 225 to 350 today, bolstered by 291 newly hired pilots and 
another 750 waiting in the wings. 
</P>
<P>
The airline had initially set a goal of 390 flights by Aug. 1 and acknowledged 
that it had to modify the schedule because of a pilot shortage. 
</P>
